did.head: Collection Summary
did.abstract: Scriptwriter and humorist. Scripts of the daytime radio series Vic and Sade written by Rhymer for airing on the National Broadcasting Company.

controlaccess.head: Selected Search Terms
controlaccess.p: The following terms have been used to index the description of this collection in the LC Catalog. They are grouped by name of person or organization, by subject or location, and by occupation and listed alphabetically.

acqinfo.head: Provenance
acqinfo.p: The radio scripts of Paul Rhymer, scriptwriter and humorist, were transferred to the Manuscript Division from the Library of Congress Copyright Office in 1972-1973.

processinfo.head: Processing History
processinfo.p: The collection was housed and described in 1973 and reprocessed in 2008. The finding aid was revised in 2009.

userestrict.head: Copyright Status
userestrict.p: The status of copyright in the unpublished writings of Paul Rhymer is governed by the Copyright Law of the United States (Title 17, U.S.C.).

accessrestrict.head: Access and Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: Restrictions apply governing the use, photoduplication, or publication of items in this collection. Consult reference staff in the Manuscript Division for information concerning these restrictions. In addition, many collections are stored off-site and advance notice is needed to retrieve these items for research use.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Researchers wishing to cite this collection should include the following information: Container number, Paul Rhymer Radio Scripts, Manuscript Division, Library of Congress, Washington, D.C.

chronitem.event: Attended Illinois Wesleyan University, Bloomington, Ill.
Moved to Chicago, Ill., and began work in continuity department at the National Broadcasting Co.
Writer of Vic and Sade daytime radio series on the National Broadcasting Co.
Vic and Sade voted the best-written program on radio
Voted best scriptwriter by radio artists
Scripted The Public Life of Cliff Norton series, a comedy show for NBC-TV

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: The radio scripts of Paul Rhymer (1905-1964) span the years 1934-1944 and consist of playscripts of Vic and Sade submitted to the Library of Congress for copyright deposit during that period. The Vic and Sade radio series, sponsored by Proctor and Gamble, aired as a daytime comedy on the National Broadcasting Company from November 1934 to December 1945 and won many awards, including for best written program on the radio in 1936.

arrangement.head: Arrangement of the Papers
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged according to year or span of years of submission and therein by copyright registration number.
